messages.text: Just left the hospital. Be home soon.
Got caught up with a patient. He keeps ripping out his IV.
Stopping at the store, want anything?
Thinking spaghetti for dinner unless you’d rather something else?
I get it, okay? But you could be a little nicer.
Well you could’ve talked to me before you sold it.
Whatever, Dad bought it for me. I wanted to keep it.
Ron and I will buy you a new one.
Can you please feed the dog?
Not tonight. I want you and Ron to spend some time together.
Please, Em. Just try to get along.
I’m scared. Mom, what do I do?
Cover you head. Where are you?
OMG Tucker’s outside! I have to save him.
Just stay calm, it’ll be over soon.
Are you in the grocery store?
It’s such a mess. The power’s out here. I’m in the dairy aisle. Lots of spilt milk, but everyone seems okay.
The bookcase fell over. And all the plates and bowls came out of the cabinets.
An older man. I think he works here.
Something fell on him. A fridge, I think, he’s in the deli section.
I don’t see Tucker. He’s not in the backyard!
NO. Stay inside. It’s not safe.
We’ll look for him when I get home. Together. Stay inside.
What if something fell on him!!
He’s probably fine. Stay inside, there could be aftershocks.
I don’t care about Ron! Come home.
Just get him inside. Be careful.
Honey, I’ve gotta step away from my phone, to help that man, okay? I’ll be a few minutes.
Just cuz ur a nurse doesn’t mean you have to help everybody!!
Honey, I have to. He’s really bleeding.
Emily, it’s Ron. Are you okay? I can’t get ahold of your mother.
I’m fine. She’s not answering me either.
I only talked to her after the first one.
She went to help some guy who’s hurt. Then everything started shaking again.
I don’t know what to do. I called her, she’s not answering!!!
I don’t know what to do???
Cell reception’s bad. Lots of trees down. Where is she?
I’m in my car a few blocks from there. I’m gonna get out and go look for her.
What do you mean? You don’t see her?
It’s hard to see anything. There’s a lot of debris.
I found her. Lot’s of people are hurt. We’re waiting for help.
The roads are dangerous. You have to stay there!
Do something then! Wake her up!
The paramedics are here. I’ll call you when I know something.
